children.name: Camber
children.tooltip: Static camber angle of the front left wheel around the vehicle's longitudinal axis. The value should relate to the equilibrium position of the test bench. A positive camber angle at the right wheel carrier equals a positive rotation around the vehicle's longitudinal axis (longitudinal axis pointing positive in driving direction). A negative camber angle at the right wheel carrier equals a negative rotation around the vehicle's longitudinal axis (longitudinal axis pointing positive in driving direction). Attention, this convention applies for MTS test benches only. For ABD test benches please set your chosen convention in the K&C converter's configuration file.

A negative spin angle at the wheel carrier equals a negative rotation around the vehicle's lateral axis (axis pointing positive leftward in driving direction). Attention, the spin angle is not to confuse with the Caster angle.
